
Overview of noun colony

The noun colony has 6 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (7) colony, settlement -- (a body of people who settle far from home but maintain ties with their homeland; inhabitants remain nationals of their home state but are not literally under the home state's system of government; "the American colony in Paris")
2. (2) colony -- (a group of organisms of the same type living or growing together)
3. Colony -- (one of the 13 British colonies that formed the original states of the United States)
4. colony -- (a place where a group of people with the same interest or occupation are concentrated; "a nudist colony"; "an artists' colony")
5. colony, dependency -- (a geographical area politically controlled by a distant country)
6. colony -- ((microbiology) a group of organisms grown from a single parent cell)
